[Made in collaboration with Sedivalle!](https://cults3d.com/en/users/Sedivalle/3d-models)
Thumbnail painted by the excellent Draconian Minipainting!

This pack contains Regular, Heavy Weapons, and Command versions of Sedivalle's Exterminators, resculpted and adjusted for printing at 8mm scale for all of your mass wargames, or scaled up as you see fit!

Options include:
***Small Arms:***
Fist, Claw and Dual Claws. 5x Poses each.

***Command:***
Champion
Banner Bearer with Fist or Bolter
Captain with choice of large or small crest

***Heavy Weapons:***
Heavy Bolters, Plasma, Heat Rays, or Disintegrator cannons.
5x Poses each. Mirroring suggested for additional variety.

If you'd like to keep up with my current projects, and support the modelling work I do, please check out my patreon at: www.patreon.com/Daffmakes

Also, check out my new discord to chat with other enjoyers of my work and post your own stuff! www.discord.gg/JuJBmc6mQs

optional heavy weaposn for your marines, add a bit of variety to your army. Doesn't effect game play and rules though.

the plasma cannon was taken from a marine speeder, heavy bolter from squat thunderer, rotor/assault cannon from dreadnought and lascannon from guardsman, so they are somewhat "legal" conversion if you care about accuracy. Ok the lascannon probably isn't accurate enough, field it at your own discretion. 

Since i can't find a melta on other epic scale unit or any other heavy ordnance in that regard, you will have to make do with these three+ og rocket.

edit: hurrah! i found a melta on squat bikers, time to turn your enemies into hot molten slag!

"Why did you make me do this? You're fighting so you can watch your brothers die around you! Think, Traitor, Think!"

Could be proxied for an objective marker or a command squad, or maybe just a morale boost :D.

Assemble the model by snipping the banner off the heavy support, and insert into the hole in the base. Paint the standing marine as desired and superglue into position.

Presupports for this are a work in progress - I'll update them as I get test prints done.

Thanks to Moonjammy and JimmyZimms for the base models and original Beaky armour, on which this is based.

Print ready for resin printers. Just import, make sure the base is on the print bed, slice then print. 2xAA and 0.02mm layer height reccommended.
These files are not intended for FDM slicers or printers.

Details like this are often irrelevant in mass battle games, but I figured they'd be a cool option.

Please bear in mind that some of these miniatures have extremely fragile parts despite my best efforts to make everything as solid as possible. Handle with care.
